#Problem
Given a string array sortedWords sorted according to the last letter of each word, return array of words sorted in lexicographical order.

For example, array is ["ate","eel","el"] and output is ["ate","el","eel"].

#Solution
```Java
class Solution {
    public String[] sortWords(String[] words) {
        int n = words.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            char last = words[i].charAt(words[i].length() - 1);
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (words[i].charAt(words[i].length() - 1) < words[j].charAt(words[j].length() - 1)) {
                    String temp = words[i];
                    words[i] = words[j];
                    words[j] = temp;
                }
            }
        }
        return words;
    }
}
```

# Code
```Java
class Solution {
    public String[] sortWords(String[] words) {
        Arrays.sort(words, new Comparator<String>() {
        public int compare(String word1, String word2) {
            return word1.charAt(word1.length() - 1) - word2.charAt(word2.length() - 1);
        }
    });
        return words;
    }
}

```

