Given the encoded array encoded = [1,2,3], return the original array. The encoded array is generated by the following algorithm:
Choose the largest number in the array and insert it at the beginning.
Choose the second largest number in the array and insert it at the end.
Repeat until there are no more elements in the array.
It is guaranteed that the input array is always valid (see algorithm explanation).
Example 1:
Input: encoded = [1,2,3]
Output: [3,2,1]
Explanation:
The first element is the largest number in the original array.
The second element is the second largest number in the original array.
The third element is the remaining number in the original array.
Constraints:
2 <= encoded.length <= 104
1 <= encoded[i] <= encoded.length
The input array is guaranteed to be produced by the given algorithm.

class Solution {
public:

    vector<int> decode(vector<int>& encoded) {
        int n=encoded.size();
        vector<int> v1(n);
        v1[n-1]=encoded[0];
        for(int i=n-2,j=1;i>=0;i--)
        {
            v1[j]=v1[j-1]-encoded[i--];
            v1[n-1]-=v1[j];
            j++;
        }
        return v1;
    }
};


